[
  {
    "startTime": 15.26,
    "endTime": 17.259,
    "text": "The things we make"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 17.26,
    "endTime": 20.26,
    "text": "have one supreme quality --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 20.26,
    "endTime": 22.26,
    "text": "they live longer than us."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 22.26,
    "endTime": 24.26,
    "text": "We perish, they survive;"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 24.26,
    "endTime": 27.26,
    "text": "we have one life, they have many lives,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 27.26,
    "endTime": 30.26,
    "text": "and in each life they can mean different things."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 30.26,
    "endTime": 33.260000000000005,
    "text": "Which means that, while we all have one biography,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 33.26,
    "endTime": 35.26,
    "text": "they have many."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 35.26,
    "endTime": 37.26,
    "text": "I want this morning to talk"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 37.26,
    "endTime": 40.26,
    "text": "about the story, the biography -- or rather the biographies --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 40.26,
    "endTime": 43.26,
    "text": "of one particular object,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 43.26,
    "endTime": 45.26,
    "text": "one remarkable thing."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 45.26,
    "endTime": 47.26,
    "text": "It doesn't, I agree,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 47.26,
    "endTime": 49.26,
    "text": "look very much."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 49.26,
    "endTime": 52.26,
    "text": "It's about the size of a rugby ball."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 52.26,
    "endTime": 54.26,
    "text": "It's made of clay,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 54.26,
    "endTime": 56.26,
    "text": "and it's been fashioned"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 56.26,
    "endTime": 59.26,
    "text": "into a cylinder shape,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 59.26,
    "endTime": 61.26,
    "text": "covered with close writing"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 61.26,
    "endTime": 64.259,
    "text": "and then baked dry in the sun."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 64.26,
    "endTime": 66.26,
    "text": "And as you can see,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 66.26,
    "endTime": 68.26,
    "text": "it's been knocked about a bit,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 68.26,
    "endTime": 70.26,
    "text": "which is not surprising"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 70.26,
    "endTime": 73.26,
    "text": "because it was made two and a half thousand years ago"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 73.26,
    "endTime": 75.26,
    "text": "and was dug up"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 75.26,
    "endTime": 77.26,
    "text": "in 1879."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 77.26,
    "endTime": 79.26,
    "text": "But today,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 79.26,
    "endTime": 81.26,
    "text": "this thing is, I believe,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 81.26,
    "endTime": 83.26,
    "text": "a major player"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 83.26,
    "endTime": 85.26,
    "text": "in the politics of the Middle East."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 85.26,
    "endTime": 87.26,
    "text": "And it's an object"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 87.26,
    "endTime": 89.26,
    "text": "with fascinating stories"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 89.26,
    "endTime": 93.26,
    "text": "and stories that are by no means over yet."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 93.26,
    "endTime": 95.26,
    "text": "The story begins"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 95.26,
    "endTime": 99.26,
    "text": "in the Iran-Iraq war"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 99.26,
    "endTime": 101.26,
    "text": "and that series of events"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 101.26,
    "endTime": 103.26,
    "text": "that culminated"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 103.26,
    "endTime": 105.26,
    "text": "in the invasion of Iraq"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 105.26,
    "endTime": 107.26,
    "text": "by foreign forces,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 107.26,
    "endTime": 109.26,
    "text": "the removal of a despotic ruler"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 109.26,
    "endTime": 112.26,
    "text": "and instant regime change."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 112.26,
    "endTime": 114.26,
    "text": "And I want to begin"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 114.26,
    "endTime": 116.26,
    "text": "with one episode from that sequence of events"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 116.26,
    "endTime": 119.26,
    "text": "that most of you would be very familiar with,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 119.26,
    "endTime": 121.26,
    "text": "Belshazzar's feast --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 121.26,
    "endTime": 123.26,
    "text": "because we're talking about the Iran-Iraq war"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 123.26,
    "endTime": 126.26,
    "text": "of 539 BC."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 126.26,
    "endTime": 128.25900000000001,
    "text": "And the parallels"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 128.259,
    "endTime": 130.259,
    "text": "between the events"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 130.259,
    "endTime": 133.26,
    "text": "of 539 BC and 2003 and in between"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 133.26,
    "endTime": 135.26,
    "text": "are startling."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 135.26,
    "endTime": 137.26,
    "text": "What you're looking at is Rembrandt's painting,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 137.26,
    "endTime": 139.26,
    "text": "now in the National Gallery in London,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 139.26,
    "endTime": 141.26,
    "text": "illustrating the text from the prophet Daniel"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 141.26,
    "endTime": 144.26,
    "text": "in the Hebrew scriptures."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 144.26,
    "endTime": 146.26,
    "text": "And you all know roughly the story."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 146.26,
    "endTime": 149.26,
    "text": "Belshazzar, the son of Nebuchadnezzar,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 149.26,
    "endTime": 152.26,
    "text": "Nebuchadnezzar who'd conquered Israel, sacked Jerusalem"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 152.26,
    "endTime": 154.26,
    "text": "and captured the people"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 154.26,
    "endTime": 156.26,
    "text": "and taken the Jews back to Babylon."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 156.26,
    "endTime": 159.26,
    "text": "Not only the Jews, he'd taken the temple vessels."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 159.26,
    "endTime": 162.26,
    "text": "He'd ransacked, desecrated the temple."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 162.26,
    "endTime": 165.26,
    "text": "And the great gold vessels of the temple in Jerusalem"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 165.26,
    "endTime": 168.26,
    "text": "had been taken to Babylon."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 168.26,
    "endTime": 170.26,
    "text": "Belshazzar, his son,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 170.26,
    "endTime": 172.26,
    "text": "decides to have a feast."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 172.26,
    "endTime": 174.26,
    "text": "And in order to make it even more exciting,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 174.26,
    "endTime": 177.26,
    "text": "he added a bit of sacrilege to the rest of the fun,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 177.26,
    "endTime": 180.26,
    "text": "and he brings out the temple vessels."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 180.26,
    "endTime": 183.26,
    "text": "He's already at war with the Iranians,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 183.26,
    "endTime": 185.26,
    "text": "with the king of Persia."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 185.26,
    "endTime": 188.26,
    "text": "And that night, Daniel tells us,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 188.26,
    "endTime": 190.26,
    "text": "at the height of the festivities"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 190.26,
    "endTime": 193.26,
    "text": "a hand appeared and wrote on the wall,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 193.26,
    "endTime": 196.26,
    "text": "\"You are weighed in the balance and found wanting,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 196.26,
    "endTime": 198.26,
    "text": "and your kingdom is handed over"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 198.26,
    "endTime": 200.26,
    "text": "to the Medes and the Persians.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 200.26,
    "endTime": 202.26,
    "text": "And that very night"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 202.26,
    "endTime": 206.26,
    "text": "Cyrus, king of the Persians, entered Babylon"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 206.26,
    "endTime": 211.26,
    "text": "and the whole regime of Belshazzar fell."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 211.26,
    "endTime": 213.26,
    "text": "It is, of course, a great moment"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 213.26,
    "endTime": 215.26,
    "text": "in the history"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 215.26,
    "endTime": 217.26,
    "text": "of the Jewish people."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 217.26,
    "endTime": 219.26,
    "text": "It's a great story. It's story we all know."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 219.26,
    "endTime": 221.26,
    "text": "\"The writing on the wall\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 221.26,
    "endTime": 224.26,
    "text": "is part of our everyday language."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 224.26,
    "endTime": 226.26,
    "text": "What happened next"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 226.26,
    "endTime": 228.26,
    "text": "was remarkable,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 228.26,
    "endTime": 230.26,
    "text": "and it's where our cylinder"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 230.26,
    "endTime": 232.26,
    "text": "enters the story."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 232.26,
    "endTime": 234.26,
    "text": "Cyrus, king of the Persians,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 234.26,
    "endTime": 236.26,
    "text": "has entered Babylon without a fight --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 236.26,
    "endTime": 238.26,
    "text": "the great empire of Babylon,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 238.26,
    "endTime": 240.26,
    "text": "which ran from central southern Iraq"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 240.26,
    "endTime": 242.26,
    "text": "to the Mediterranean,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 242.26,
    "endTime": 244.26,
    "text": "falls to Cyrus."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 244.26,
    "endTime": 248.26,
    "text": "And Cyrus makes a declaration."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 248.26,
    "endTime": 251.26,
    "text": "And that is what this cylinder is,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 251.26,
    "endTime": 254.26,
    "text": "the declaration made by the ruler guided by God"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 254.26,
    "endTime": 258.26,
    "text": "who had toppled the Iraqi despot"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 258.26,
    "endTime": 260.26,
    "text": "and was going to bring freedom to the people."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 260.26,
    "endTime": 262.26,
    "text": "In ringing Babylonian --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 262.26,
    "endTime": 264.26,
    "text": "it was written in Babylonian --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 264.26,
    "endTime": 267.26,
    "text": "he says, \"I am Cyrus, king of all the universe,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 267.26,
    "endTime": 269.26,
    "text": "the great king, the powerful king,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 269.26,
    "endTime": 273.26,
    "text": "king of Babylon, king of the four quarters of the world.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 273.26,
    "endTime": 276.26,
    "text": "They're not shy of hyperbole as you can see."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 276.26,
    "endTime": 278.26,
    "text": "This is probably"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 278.26,
    "endTime": 280.26,
    "text": "the first real press release"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 280.26,
    "endTime": 282.26,
    "text": "by a victorious army"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 282.26,
    "endTime": 284.26,
    "text": "that we've got."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 284.26,
    "endTime": 286.26,
    "text": "And it's written, as we'll see in due course,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 286.26,
    "endTime": 289.26,
    "text": "by very skilled P.R. consultants."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 289.26,
    "endTime": 292.26,
    "text": "So the hyperbole is not actually surprising."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 292.26,
    "endTime": 294.26,
    "text": "And what is the great king, the powerful king,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 294.26,
    "endTime": 297.26,
    "text": "the king of the four quarters of the world going to do?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 297.26,
    "endTime": 300.26,
    "text": "He goes on to say that, having conquered Babylon,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 300.26,
    "endTime": 303.26,
    "text": "he will at once let all the peoples"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 303.26,
    "endTime": 305.26,
    "text": "that the Babylonians -- Nebuchadnezzar and Belshazzar --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 305.26,
    "endTime": 307.26,
    "text": "have captured and enslaved"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 307.26,
    "endTime": 309.26,
    "text": "go free."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 309.26,
    "endTime": 311.26,
    "text": "He'll let them return to their countries."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 311.26,
    "endTime": 313.26,
    "text": "And more important,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 313.26,
    "endTime": 315.26,
    "text": "he will let them all recover"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 315.26,
    "endTime": 317.26,
    "text": "the gods, the statues,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 317.26,
    "endTime": 319.26,
    "text": "the temple vessels"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 319.26,
    "endTime": 321.26,
    "text": "that had been confiscated."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 321.26,
    "endTime": 324.26,
    "text": "All the peoples that the Babylonians had repressed and removed"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 324.26,
    "endTime": 326.26,
    "text": "will go home,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 326.26,
    "endTime": 329.26,
    "text": "and they'll take with them their gods."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 329.26,
    "endTime": 332.26,
    "text": "And they'll be able to restore their altars"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 332.26,
    "endTime": 334.26,
    "text": "and to worship their gods"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 334.26,
    "endTime": 337.26,
    "text": "in their own way, in their own place."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 337.26,
    "endTime": 339.26,
    "text": "This is the decree,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 339.26,
    "endTime": 342.26,
    "text": "this object is the evidence"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 342.26,
    "endTime": 344.26,
    "text": "for the fact that the Jews,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 344.26,
    "endTime": 346.26,
    "text": "after the exile in Babylon,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 346.26,
    "endTime": 349.26,
    "text": "the years they'd spent sitting by the waters of Babylon,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 349.26,
    "endTime": 352.26,
    "text": "weeping when they remembered Jerusalem,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 352.26,
    "endTime": 355.26,
    "text": "those Jews were allowed to go home."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 355.26,
    "endTime": 357.26,
    "text": "They were allowed to return to Jerusalem"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 357.26,
    "endTime": 359.26,
    "text": "and to rebuild the temple."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 359.26,
    "endTime": 361.26,
    "text": "It's a central document"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 361.26,
    "endTime": 363.26,
    "text": "in Jewish history."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 363.26,
    "endTime": 367.26,
    "text": "And the Book of Chronicles, the Book of Ezra in the Hebrew scriptures"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 367.26,
    "endTime": 369.26,
    "text": "reported in ringing terms."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 369.26,
    "endTime": 371.26,
    "text": "This is the Jewish version"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 371.26,
    "endTime": 373.26,
    "text": "of the same story."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 373.26,
    "endTime": 375.26,
    "text": "\"Thus said Cyrus, king of Persia,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 375.26,
    "endTime": 378.26,
    "text": "'All the kingdoms of the earth have the Lord God of heaven given thee,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 378.26,
    "endTime": 380.26,
    "text": "and he has charged me"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 380.26,
    "endTime": 382.26,
    "text": "to build him a house in Jerusalem."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 382.26,
    "endTime": 384.26,
    "text": "Who is there among you of his people?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 384.26,
    "endTime": 386.26,
    "text": "The Lord God be with him,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 386.26,
    "endTime": 389.26,
    "text": "and let him go up.'\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 389.26,
    "endTime": 391.26,
    "text": "\"Go up\" -- aaleh."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 391.26,
    "endTime": 394.26,
    "text": "The central element, still,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 394.26,
    "endTime": 396.26,
    "text": "of the notion of return,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 396.26,
    "endTime": 398.26,
    "text": "a central part"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 398.26,
    "endTime": 400.26,
    "text": "of the life of Judaism."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 400.26,
    "endTime": 402.26,
    "text": "As you all know, that return from exile,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 402.26,
    "endTime": 404.26,
    "text": "the second temple,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 404.26,
    "endTime": 406.26,
    "text": "reshaped Judaism."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 406.26,
    "endTime": 408.26,
    "text": "And that change,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 408.26,
    "endTime": 410.26,
    "text": "that great historic moment,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 410.26,
    "endTime": 414.26,
    "text": "was made possible by Cyrus, the king of Persia,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 414.26,
    "endTime": 417.26,
    "text": "reported for us in Hebrew in scripture"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 417.26,
    "endTime": 420.26,
    "text": "and in Babylonian in clay."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 420.26,
    "endTime": 422.26,
    "text": "Two great texts,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 422.26,
    "endTime": 424.26,
    "text": "what about the politics?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 424.26,
    "endTime": 426.26,
    "text": "What was going on"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 426.26,
    "endTime": 429.26,
    "text": "was the fundamental shift in Middle Eastern history."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 429.26,
    "endTime": 432.26,
    "text": "The empire of Iran, the Medes and the Persians,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 432.26,
    "endTime": 434.26,
    "text": "united under Cyrus,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 434.26,
    "endTime": 438.26,
    "text": "became the first great world empire."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 438.26,
    "endTime": 441.26,
    "text": "Cyrus begins in the 530s BC."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 441.26,
    "endTime": 445.26,
    "text": "And by the time of his son Darius,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 445.26,
    "endTime": 448.26,
    "text": "the whole of the eastern Mediterranean"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 448.26,
    "endTime": 450.26,
    "text": "is under Persian control."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 450.26,
    "endTime": 452.26,
    "text": "This empire is, in fact,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 452.26,
    "endTime": 454.26,
    "text": "the Middle East as we now know it,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 454.26,
    "endTime": 457.26,
    "text": "and it's what shapes the Middle East as we now know it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 457.26,
    "endTime": 459.26,
    "text": "It was the largest empire the world had known until then."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 459.26,
    "endTime": 461.26,
    "text": "Much more important,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 461.26,
    "endTime": 463.26,
    "text": "it was the first"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 463.26,
    "endTime": 465.26,
    "text": "multicultural, multifaith state"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 465.26,
    "endTime": 467.26,
    "text": "on a huge scale."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 467.26,
    "endTime": 469.26,
    "text": "And it had to be run in a quite new way."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 469.26,
    "endTime": 471.26,
    "text": "It had to be run in different languages."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 471.26,
    "endTime": 474.26,
    "text": "The fact that this decree is in Babylonian says one thing."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 474.26,
    "endTime": 476.26,
    "text": "And it had to recognize their different habits,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 476.26,
    "endTime": 479.26,
    "text": "different peoples, different religions, different faiths."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 479.26,
    "endTime": 482.26,
    "text": "All of those are respected by Cyrus."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 482.26,
    "endTime": 484.26,
    "text": "Cyrus sets up a model"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 484.26,
    "endTime": 486.26,
    "text": "of how you run"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 486.26,
    "endTime": 491.26,
    "text": "a great multinational, multifaith, multicultural society."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 491.26,
    "endTime": 493.26,
    "text": "And the result of that"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 493.26,
    "endTime": 496.26,
    "text": "was an empire that included the areas you see on the screen,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 496.26,
    "endTime": 499.26,
    "text": "and which survived for 200 years of stability"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 499.26,
    "endTime": 502.26,
    "text": "until it was shattered by Alexander."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 502.26,
    "endTime": 504.26,
    "text": "It left a dream of the Middle East as a unit,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 504.26,
    "endTime": 506.26,
    "text": "and a unit where people of different faiths"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 506.26,
    "endTime": 508.26,
    "text": "could live together."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 508.26,
    "endTime": 510.26,
    "text": "The Greek invasions ended that."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 510.26,
    "endTime": 513.26,
    "text": "And of course, Alexander couldn't sustain a government"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 513.26,
    "endTime": 515.26,
    "text": "and it fragmented."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 515.26,
    "endTime": 517.26,
    "text": "But what Cyrus represented"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 517.26,
    "endTime": 519.26,
    "text": "remained absolutely central."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 519.26,
    "endTime": 522.26,
    "text": "The Greek historian Xenophon"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 522.26,
    "endTime": 524.26,
    "text": "wrote his book \"Cyropaedia\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 524.26,
    "endTime": 526.26,
    "text": "promoting Cyrus as the great ruler."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 526.26,
    "endTime": 529.26,
    "text": "And throughout European culture afterward,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 529.26,
    "endTime": 532.26,
    "text": "Cyrus remained the model."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 532.26,
    "endTime": 534.26,
    "text": "This is a 16th century image"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 534.26,
    "endTime": 536.26,
    "text": "to show you how widespread"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 536.26,
    "endTime": 539.26,
    "text": "his veneration actually was."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 539.26,
    "endTime": 541.26,
    "text": "And Xenophon's book on Cyrus"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 541.26,
    "endTime": 544.26,
    "text": "on how you ran a diverse society"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 544.26,
    "endTime": 546.26,
    "text": "was one of the great textbooks"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 546.26,
    "endTime": 548.26,
    "text": "that inspired the Founding Fathers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 548.26,
    "endTime": 550.26,
    "text": "of the American Revolution."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 550.26,
    "endTime": 552.26,
    "text": "Jefferson was a great admirer --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 552.26,
    "endTime": 554.26,
    "text": "the ideals of Cyrus"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 554.26,
    "endTime": 556.26,
    "text": "obviously speaking to those 18th century ideals"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 556.26,
    "endTime": 558.26,
    "text": "of how you create religious tolerance"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 558.26,
    "endTime": 561.26,
    "text": "in a new state."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 563.26,
    "endTime": 565.26,
    "text": "Meanwhile, back in Babylon,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 565.26,
    "endTime": 567.26,
    "text": "things had not been going well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 567.26,
    "endTime": 570.26,
    "text": "After Alexander, the other empires,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 570.26,
    "endTime": 573.26,
    "text": "Babylon declines, falls into ruins,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 573.26,
    "endTime": 577.26,
    "text": "and all the traces of the great Babylonian empire are lost --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 577.26,
    "endTime": 579.26,
    "text": "until 1879"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 579.26,
    "endTime": 582.26,
    "text": "when the cylinder is discovered"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 582.26,
    "endTime": 585.26,
    "text": "by a British Museum exhibition digging in Babylon."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 585.26,
    "endTime": 588.26,
    "text": "And it enters now another story."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 588.26,
    "endTime": 590.26,
    "text": "It enters that great debate"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 590.26,
    "endTime": 592.26,
    "text": "in the middle of the 19th century:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 592.26,
    "endTime": 595.26,
    "text": "Are the scriptures reliable? Can we trust them?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 595.26,
    "endTime": 597.26,
    "text": "We only knew"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 597.26,
    "endTime": 599.26,
    "text": "about the return of the Jews and the decree of Cyrus"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 599.26,
    "endTime": 601.26,
    "text": "from the Hebrew scriptures."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 601.26,
    "endTime": 603.26,
    "text": "No other evidence."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 603.26,
    "endTime": 605.26,
    "text": "Suddenly, this appeared."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 605.26,
    "endTime": 607.26,
    "text": "And great excitement"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 607.26,
    "endTime": 609.26,
    "text": "to a world where those who believed in the scriptures"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 609.26,
    "endTime": 611.26,
    "text": "had had their faith in creation shaken"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 611.26,
    "endTime": 613.26,
    "text": "by evolution, by geology,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 613.26,
    "endTime": 615.26,
    "text": "here was evidence"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 615.26,
    "endTime": 617.26,
    "text": "that the scriptures were historically true."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 617.26,
    "endTime": 620.26,
    "text": "It's a great 19th century moment."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 620.26,
    "endTime": 625.26,
    "text": "But -- and this, of course, is where it becomes complicated --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 625.26,
    "endTime": 627.26,
    "text": "the facts were true,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 627.26,
    "endTime": 630.26,
    "text": "hurrah for archeology,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 630.26,
    "endTime": 633.26,
    "text": "but the interpretation was rather more complicated."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 633.26,
    "endTime": 636.26,
    "text": "Because the cylinder account and the Hebrew Bible account"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 636.26,
    "endTime": 638.26,
    "text": "differ in one key respect."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 638.26,
    "endTime": 640.26,
    "text": "The Babylonian cylinder"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 640.26,
    "endTime": 642.26,
    "text": "is written by the priests"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 642.26,
    "endTime": 644.26,
    "text": "of the great god of Bablyon, Marduk."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 644.26,
    "endTime": 646.26,
    "text": "And, not surprisingly,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 646.26,
    "endTime": 648.26,
    "text": "they tell you that all this was done by Marduk."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 648.26,
    "endTime": 651.26,
    "text": "\"Marduk, we hold, called Cyrus by his name.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 651.26,
    "endTime": 654.26,
    "text": "Marduk takes Cyrus by the hand,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 654.26,
    "endTime": 656.26,
    "text": "calls him to shepherd his people"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 656.26,
    "endTime": 659.26,
    "text": "and gives him the rule of Babylon."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 659.26,
    "endTime": 661.26,
    "text": "Marduk tells Cyrus"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 661.26,
    "endTime": 663.26,
    "text": "that he will do these great, generous things"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 663.26,
    "endTime": 665.26,
    "text": "of setting the people free."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 665.26,
    "endTime": 667.26,
    "text": "And this is why we should all be grateful to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 667.26,
    "endTime": 669.26,
    "text": "and worship Marduk."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 669.26,
    "endTime": 671.26,
    "text": "The Hebrew writers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 671.26,
    "endTime": 673.26,
    "text": "in the Old Testament,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 673.26,
    "endTime": 676.26,
    "text": "you will not be surprised to learn,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 676.26,
    "endTime": 678.26,
    "text": "take a rather different view of this."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 678.26,
    "endTime": 680.26,
    "text": "For them, of course, it can't possibly by Marduk"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 680.26,
    "endTime": 682.26,
    "text": "that made all this happen."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 682.26,
    "endTime": 684.26,
    "text": "It can only be Jehovah."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 684.26,
    "endTime": 686.26,
    "text": "And so in Isaiah,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 686.26,
    "endTime": 688.26,
    "text": "we have the wonderful texts"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 688.26,
    "endTime": 690.26,
    "text": "giving all the credit of this,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 690.26,
    "endTime": 691.26,
    "text": "not to Marduk"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 691.26,
    "endTime": 694.26,
    "text": "but to the Lord God of Israel --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 694.26,
    "endTime": 696.26,
    "text": "the Lord God of Israel"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 696.26,
    "endTime": 698.26,
    "text": "who also called Cyrus by name,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 698.26,
    "endTime": 701.26,
    "text": "also takes Cyrus by the hand"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 701.26,
    "endTime": 703.26,
    "text": "and talks of him shepherding his people."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 703.26,
    "endTime": 705.26,
    "text": "It's a remarkable example"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 705.26,
    "endTime": 709.26,
    "text": "of two different priestly appropriations of the same event,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 709.26,
    "endTime": 711.26,
    "text": "two different religious takeovers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 711.26,
    "endTime": 713.26,
    "text": "of a political fact."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 713.26,
    "endTime": 715.26,
    "text": "God, we know,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 715.26,
    "endTime": 717.26,
    "text": "is usually on the side of the big battalions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 717.26,
    "endTime": 720.26,
    "text": "The question is, which god was it?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 720.26,
    "endTime": 722.26,
    "text": "And the debate unsettles"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 722.26,
    "endTime": 724.26,
    "text": "everybody in the 19th century"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 724.26,
    "endTime": 726.26,
    "text": "to realize that the Hebrew scriptures"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 726.26,
    "endTime": 729.26,
    "text": "are part of a much wider world of religion."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 729.26,
    "endTime": 731.26,
    "text": "And it's quite clear"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 731.26,
    "endTime": 734.26,
    "text": "the cylinder is older than the text of Isaiah,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 734.26,
    "endTime": 736.26,
    "text": "and yet, Jehovah is speaking"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 736.26,
    "endTime": 738.26,
    "text": "in words very similar"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 738.26,
    "endTime": 740.26,
    "text": "to those used by Marduk."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 740.26,
    "endTime": 743.26,
    "text": "And there's a slight sense that Isaiah knows this,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 743.26,
    "endTime": 745.26,
    "text": "because he says,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 745.26,
    "endTime": 748.26,
    "text": "this is God speaking, of course,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 748.26,
    "endTime": 750.26,
    "text": "\"I have called thee by thy name"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 750.26,
    "endTime": 752.26,
    "text": "though thou hast not known me.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 752.26,
    "endTime": 754.26,
    "text": "I think it's recognized"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 754.26,
    "endTime": 756.26,
    "text": "that Cyrus doesn't realize"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 756.26,
    "endTime": 759.26,
    "text": "that he's acting under orders from Jehovah."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 759.26,
    "endTime": 762.26,
    "text": "And equally, he'd have been surprised that he was acting under orders from Marduk."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 762.26,
    "endTime": 764.26,
    "text": "Because interestingly, of course,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 764.26,
    "endTime": 766.26,
    "text": "Cyrus is a good Iranian"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 766.26,
    "endTime": 768.26,
    "text": "with a totally different set of gods"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 768.26,
    "endTime": 770.26,
    "text": "who are not mentioned in any of these texts."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 770.26,
    "endTime": 772.26,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 772.26,
    "endTime": 774.26,
    "text": "That's 1879."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 774.26,
    "endTime": 776.26,
    "text": "40 years on"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 776.26,
    "endTime": 779.26,
    "text": "and we're in 1917,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 779.26,
    "endTime": 781.26,
    "text": "and the cylinder enters a different world."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 781.26,
    "endTime": 783.26,
    "text": "This time, the real politics"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 783.26,
    "endTime": 785.26,
    "text": "of the contemporary world --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 785.26,
    "endTime": 788.26,
    "text": "the year of the Balfour Declaration,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 788.26,
    "endTime": 791.26,
    "text": "the year when the new imperial power in the Middle East, Britain,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 791.26,
    "endTime": 793.26,
    "text": "decides that it will declare"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 793.26,
    "endTime": 795.26,
    "text": "a Jewish national home,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 795.26,
    "endTime": 797.26,
    "text": "it will allow"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 797.26,
    "endTime": 799.26,
    "text": "the Jews to return."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 799.26,
    "endTime": 801.26,
    "text": "And the response to this"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 801.26,
    "endTime": 804.26,
    "text": "by the Jewish population in Eastern Europe is rhapsodic."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 804.26,
    "endTime": 806.26,
    "text": "And across Eastern Europe,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 806.26,
    "endTime": 808.26,
    "text": "Jews display pictures of Cyrus"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 808.26,
    "endTime": 810.26,
    "text": "and of George V"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 810.26,
    "endTime": 812.26,
    "text": "side by side --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 812.26,
    "endTime": 814.26,
    "text": "the two great rulers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 814.26,
    "endTime": 817.26,
    "text": "who have allowed the return to Jerusalem."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 817.26,
    "endTime": 820.26,
    "text": "And the Cyrus cylinder comes back into public view"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 820.26,
    "endTime": 822.26,
    "text": "and the text of this"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 822.26,
    "endTime": 825.26,
    "text": "as a demonstration of why what is going to happen"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 825.26,
    "endTime": 828.26,
    "text": "after the war is over in 1918"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 828.26,
    "endTime": 831.26,
    "text": "is part of a divine plan."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 831.26,
    "endTime": 833.26,
    "text": "You all know what happened."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 833.26,
    "endTime": 836.26,
    "text": "The state of Israel is setup,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 836.26,
    "endTime": 839.26,
    "text": "and 50 years later, in the late 60s,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 839.26,
    "endTime": 842.26,
    "text": "it's clear that Britain's role as the imperial power is over."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 842.26,
    "endTime": 845.26,
    "text": "And another story of the cylinder begins."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 845.26,
    "endTime": 847.26,
    "text": "The region, the U.K. and the U.S. decide,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 847.26,
    "endTime": 850.26,
    "text": "has to be kept safe from communism,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 850.26,
    "endTime": 853.26,
    "text": "and the superpower that will be created to do this"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 853.26,
    "endTime": 855.26,
    "text": "would be Iran, the Shah."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 855.26,
    "endTime": 858.26,
    "text": "And so the Shah invents an Iranian history,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 858.26,
    "endTime": 860.26,
    "text": "or a return to Iranian history,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 860.26,
    "endTime": 863.26,
    "text": "that puts him in the center of a great tradition"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 863.26,
    "endTime": 865.26,
    "text": "and produces coins"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 865.26,
    "endTime": 867.26,
    "text": "showing himself"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 867.26,
    "endTime": 869.26,
    "text": "with the Cyrus cylinder."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 869.26,
    "endTime": 872.26,
    "text": "When he has his great celebrations in Persepolis,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 872.26,
    "endTime": 874.26,
    "text": "he summons the cylinder"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 874.26,
    "endTime": 877.26,
    "text": "and the cylinder is lent by the British Museum, goes to Tehran,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 877.26,
    "endTime": 879.26,
    "text": "and is part of those great celebrations"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 879.26,
    "endTime": 882.26,
    "text": "of the Pahlavi dynasty."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 882.26,
    "endTime": 885.26,
    "text": "Cyrus cylinder: guarantor of the Shah."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 885.26,
    "endTime": 888.26,
    "text": "10 years later, another story:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 888.26,
    "endTime": 890.26,
    "text": "Iranian Revolution, 1979."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 890.26,
    "endTime": 892.26,
    "text": "Islamic revolution, no more Cyrus;"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 892.26,
    "endTime": 894.26,
    "text": "we're not interested in that history,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 894.26,
    "endTime": 897.26,
    "text": "we're interested in Islamic Iran --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 897.26,
    "endTime": 899.26,
    "text": "until Iraq,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 899.26,
    "endTime": 902.26,
    "text": "the new superpower that we've all decided should be in the region,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 902.26,
    "endTime": 904.26,
    "text": "attacks."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 904.26,
    "endTime": 906.26,
    "text": "Then another Iran-Iraq war."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 906.26,
    "endTime": 908.26,
    "text": "And it becomes critical for the Iranians"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 908.26,
    "endTime": 911.26,
    "text": "to remember their great past,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 911.26,
    "endTime": 913.26,
    "text": "their great past"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 913.26,
    "endTime": 916.26,
    "text": "when they fought Iraq and won."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 916.26,
    "endTime": 918.26,
    "text": "It becomes critical to find a symbol"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 918.26,
    "endTime": 921.26,
    "text": "that will pull together all Iranians --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 921.26,
    "endTime": 923.26,
    "text": "Muslims and non-Muslims,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 923.26,
    "endTime": 926.26,
    "text": "Christians, Zoroastrians, Jews living in Iran,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 926.26,
    "endTime": 928.26,
    "text": "people who are devout, not devout."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 928.26,
    "endTime": 931.26,
    "text": "And the obvious emblem is Cyrus."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 931.26,
    "endTime": 934.26,
    "text": "So when the British Museum and Tehran National Musuem"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 934.26,
    "endTime": 936.26,
    "text": "cooperate and work together, as we've been doing,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 936.26,
    "endTime": 938.26,
    "text": "the Iranians ask for one thing only"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 938.26,
    "endTime": 940.26,
    "text": "as a loan."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 940.26,
    "endTime": 942.26,
    "text": "It's the only object they want."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 942.26,
    "endTime": 944.26,
    "text": "They want to borrow the Cyrus cylinder."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 944.26,
    "endTime": 946.26,
    "text": "And last year,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 946.26,
    "endTime": 950.26,
    "text": "the Cyrus cylinder went to Tehran"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 950.26,
    "endTime": 953.26,
    "text": "for the second time."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 953.26,
    "endTime": 956.26,
    "text": "It's shown being presented here, put into its case"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 956.26,
    "endTime": 959.26,
    "text": "by the director of the National Museum of Tehran,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 959.26,
    "endTime": 962.26,
    "text": "one of the many women in Iran in very senior positions,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 962.26,
    "endTime": 964.26,
    "text": "Mrs. Ardakani."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 964.26,
    "endTime": 966.26,
    "text": "It was a huge event."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 966.26,
    "endTime": 969.26,
    "text": "This is the other side of that same picture."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 969.26,
    "endTime": 972.26,
    "text": "It's seen in Tehran"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 972.26,
    "endTime": 974.26,
    "text": "by between one and two million people"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 974.26,
    "endTime": 976.26,
    "text": "in the space of a few months."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 976.26,
    "endTime": 978.26,
    "text": "This is beyond any blockbuster exhibition"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 978.26,
    "endTime": 980.26,
    "text": "in the West."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 980.26,
    "endTime": 983.26,
    "text": "And it's the subject of a huge debate"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 983.26,
    "endTime": 986.26,
    "text": "about what this cylinder means, what Cyrus means,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 986.26,
    "endTime": 989.26,
    "text": "but above all, Cyrus as articulated through this cylinder --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 989.26,
    "endTime": 992.26,
    "text": "Cyrus as the defender of the homeland,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 992.26,
    "endTime": 994.26,
    "text": "the champion, of course, of Iranian identity"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 994.26,
    "endTime": 996.26,
    "text": "and of the Iranian peoples,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 996.26,
    "endTime": 998.26,
    "text": "tolerant of all faiths."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 998.26,
    "endTime": 1000.26,
    "text": "And in the current Iran,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1000.26,
    "endTime": 1003.26,
    "text": "Zoroastrians and Christians have guaranteed places"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1003.26,
    "endTime": 1006.26,
    "text": "in the Iranian parliament, something to be very, very proud of."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1006.26,
    "endTime": 1009.26,
    "text": "To see this object in Tehran,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1009.26,
    "endTime": 1011.26,
    "text": "thousands of Jews living in Iran"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1011.26,
    "endTime": 1013.26,
    "text": "came to Tehran to see it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1013.26,
    "endTime": 1015.26,
    "text": "It became a great emblem,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1015.26,
    "endTime": 1017.26,
    "text": "a great subject of debate"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1017.26,
    "endTime": 1020.26,
    "text": "about what Iran is at home and abroad."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1020.26,
    "endTime": 1023.26,
    "text": "Is Iran still to be the defender of the oppressed?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1023.26,
    "endTime": 1025.26,
    "text": "Will Iran set free the people"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1025.26,
    "endTime": 1028.26,
    "text": "that the tyrants have enslaved and expropriated?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1028.26,
    "endTime": 1031.26,
    "text": "This is heady national rhetoric,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1031.26,
    "endTime": 1033.26,
    "text": "and it was all put together"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1033.26,
    "endTime": 1035.26,
    "text": "in a great pageant"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1035.26,
    "endTime": 1037.26,
    "text": "launching the return."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1037.26,
    "endTime": 1040.26,
    "text": "Here you see this out-sized Cyrus cylinder on the stage"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1040.26,
    "endTime": 1043.26,
    "text": "with great figures from Iranian history"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1043.26,
    "endTime": 1045.26,
    "text": "gathering to take their place"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1045.26,
    "endTime": 1048.26,
    "text": "in the heritage of Iran."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1048.26,
    "endTime": 1050.26,
    "text": "It was a narrative presented"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1050.26,
    "endTime": 1053.26,
    "text": "by the president himself."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1053.26,
    "endTime": 1055.26,
    "text": "And for me,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1055.26,
    "endTime": 1057.26,
    "text": "to take this object to Iran,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1057.26,
    "endTime": 1059.26,
    "text": "to be allowed to take this object to Iran"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1059.26,
    "endTime": 1061.26,
    "text": "was to be allowed to be part"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1061.26,
    "endTime": 1063.26,
    "text": "of an extraordinary debate"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1063.26,
    "endTime": 1065.26,
    "text": "led at the highest levels"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1065.26,
    "endTime": 1067.26,
    "text": "about what Iran is,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1067.26,
    "endTime": 1070.26,
    "text": "what different Irans there are"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1070.26,
    "endTime": 1072.26,
    "text": "and how the different histories of Iran"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1072.26,
    "endTime": 1075.26,
    "text": "might shape the world today."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1075.26,
    "endTime": 1078.26,
    "text": "It's a debate that's still continuing,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1078.26,
    "endTime": 1080.26,
    "text": "and it will continue to rumble,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1080.26,
    "endTime": 1082.26,
    "text": "because this object"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1082.26,
    "endTime": 1084.26,
    "text": "is one of the great declarations"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1084.26,
    "endTime": 1086.26,
    "text": "of a human aspiration."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1086.26,
    "endTime": 1090.26,
    "text": "It stands with the American constitution."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1090.26,
    "endTime": 1093.26,
    "text": "It certainly says far more about real freedoms"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1093.26,
    "endTime": 1095.26,
    "text": "than Magna Carta."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1095.26,
    "endTime": 1098.26,
    "text": "It is a document that can mean so many things,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1098.26,
    "endTime": 1101.26,
    "text": "for Iran and for the region."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1101.26,
    "endTime": 1103.26,
    "text": "A replica of this"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1103.26,
    "endTime": 1105.26,
    "text": "is at the United Nations."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1105.26,
    "endTime": 1108.26,
    "text": "In New York this autumn, it will be present"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1108.26,
    "endTime": 1110.26,
    "text": "when the great debates"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1110.26,
    "endTime": 1113.26,
    "text": "about the future of the Middle East take place."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1113.26,
    "endTime": 1115.26,
    "text": "And I want to finish by asking you"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1115.26,
    "endTime": 1117.26,
    "text": "what the next story will be"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1117.26,
    "endTime": 1119.26,
    "text": "in which this object figures."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1119.26,
    "endTime": 1121.26,
    "text": "It will appear, certainly,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1121.26,
    "endTime": 1123.26,
    "text": "in many more Middle Eastern stories."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1123.26,
    "endTime": 1125.26,
    "text": "And what story of the Middle East,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1125.26,
    "endTime": 1127.26,
    "text": "what story of the world,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1127.26,
    "endTime": 1129.26,
    "text": "do you want to see"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1129.26,
    "endTime": 1131.26,
    "text": "reflecting what is said,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1131.26,
    "endTime": 1133.26,
    "text": "what is expressed in this cylinder?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1133.26,
    "endTime": 1135.26,
    "text": "The right of peoples"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1135.26,
    "endTime": 1137.26,
    "text": "to live together in the same state,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1137.26,
    "endTime": 1139.26,
    "text": "worshiping differently, freely --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1139.26,
    "endTime": 1141.26,
    "text": "a Middle East, a world,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1141.26,
    "endTime": 1143.26,
    "text": "in which religion is not the subject of division"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1143.26,
    "endTime": 1146.26,
    "text": "or of debate."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1146.26,
    "endTime": 1149.26,
    "text": "In the world of the Middle East at the moment,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1149.26,
    "endTime": 1152.26,
    "text": "the debates are, as you know, shrill."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1152.26,
    "endTime": 1154.26,
    "text": "But I think it's possible"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1154.26,
    "endTime": 1158.26,
    "text": "that the most powerful and the wisest voice of all of them"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1158.26,
    "endTime": 1160.26,
    "text": "may well be the voice"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1160.26,
    "endTime": 1162.26,
    "text": "of this mute thing,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1162.26,
    "endTime": 1164.26,
    "text": "the Cyrus cylinder."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1164.26,
    "endTime": 1166.26,
    "text": "Thank you."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1166.26,
    "endTime": 1170.26,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  }
]